{"word":"ὑπερηνορέων","slug":"ὑπερηνορέων","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<entryFree id=\"n107542\" key=\"u(perhnore/wn\" type=\"main\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"entryFree\"> <orth extent=\"suff\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">ὑπερηνορ-έων</orth>, <itype lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"itype\">οντος</itype>, <gen lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gen\">ὁ</gen>, <sense id=\"n107542.0\" n=\"A\" level=\"1\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">exceedingly manly</tr_>: but always used in bad sense (though <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ἠνορέη</foreign> is <xr opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"xr\"> <lbl opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"lbl\">=</lbl> <ref targOrder=\"U\" lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"ref\">ἀνδρεία</ref></xr>, <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">manliness, courage), overbearing, overweening,</tr_> of the Trojans, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.perseus-grc1:4:176\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Il.\">Il.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">4.176</biblScope> </bibl>; of Deïphobus (the Trojan), <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.perseus-grc1:13:258\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">13.258</biblScope> </bibl>; of the Cyclopes, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg002.perseus-grc1:6:5\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Od.\">Od.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">6.5</biblScope> </bibl>; in <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Od.\">Od.</a></author> </bibl> mostly of the suitors, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg002.perseus-grc1:17:482\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">17.482</biblScope></bibl>, al.; <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">κακῶς ὑπερηνορέοντες</quote_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg002.perseus-grc1:2:266\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">2.266</biblScope></bibl></cit>, cf. <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg002.perseus-grc1:4:766\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">4.766</biblScope></bibl>. </sense> <sense n=\"II\" id=\"n107542.1\" level=\"2\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> Com., <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">thinking oneself more than man,</tr_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0019.tlg005.perseus-grc1:53\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Ar.\">Ar.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Pax\">Pax</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">53</biblScope></bibl>. (No Verb <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ὑπερηνορέω</foreign> occurs: cf. <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ὑπερμενέων.</foreign>)</sense> </entryFree>"}]}